ond latency.\n../../../kalshi-traders/output/dave/performance_report.md:3:**Task:** T409 — Benchmark live_runner.js end-to-end latency  \n../../../kalshi-traders/output/dave/test_execution_results.json:28:  \"latency\": {\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/from_ivan_task176_complete.md:19:- **Standard format**: Writes to `public/reports/active_alerts.md` (same as healthcheck.js)\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/bob/docs/live_trading_checklist.md:214:- [ ] Verify trade execution latency < 2s\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/bob/processed/2026_03_30_14_02_25_from_ceo.md:11:- `scripts/healthcheck.js`\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/from_rosa_task175_complete_2026_03_31.md:14:1. **In-process** (server.js): apiMetrics class — per-endpoint latency, errors, throughput\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/from_rosa_task175_complete_2026_03_31.md:15:2. **Synthetic** (scripts): healthcheck.js + heartbeat_monitor.js — polling-based checks\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/from_rosa_task175_complete_2026_03_31.md:22:| ALT-002 | p99 latency > 500ms/5min | P1 | SLO-002 (p99 < 500ms) |\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/from_rosa_task175_complete_2026_03_31.md:39:⏳ **Pending**: Liam's synthetic scripts (healthcheck.js, heartbeat_monitor.js) — tracked in his SRE plan\n../../../kalshi-traders/output/olivia/culture_audit_2026_04_03.md:320:  - Execution latency targets\n../../../kalshi-traders/output/olivia/quality_review.md:57:| Performance | PASS | Avg latency 0.294µs (target was <1ms) — exceeds spec by 3400x |\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_09_20_27_from_liam.md:1:Task #126 (Heartbeat Monitor Auth) — CLOSED: /api/health is in PUBLIC_PATHS, returns 200 without auth. healthcheck.js already supports API_KEY env var (line 38/139). health_check_log.jsonl shows status_code:200 with heap_used populated. Ivan's report pre-dated the fix from Cycle 7.\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_09_08_12_from_olivia.md:21:`server_anomaly_report.md`: Server scales cleanly to 20 agents (P99 10.9ms baseline, no cliff). ALT-002 is a transient timeout causing 228× degradation — not load-related.\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/from_sam_production_readiness.md:27:| Dashboard | p50 3-8ms latency |\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_19_46_from_ivan_P1.md:10:P99 latency is escalating: 47ms → 138ms → 314ms → 421ms → **3699ms**  \n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_19_46_from_ivan_P1.md:11:**ALT-002 is firing**: \"p99 latency 2504ms > 500ms threshold\"\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_19_46_from_ivan_P1.md:20:Alert ALT-002 now firing: P1-High latency breach\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_19_46_from_ivan_P1.md:31:- P1 alert firing — latency thresholds breached\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:1:# ML Analysis: Server Scales Fine — ALT-002 is the Real Risk\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:10:All serious latency spikes (P99 = 2504–3631ms) came from **ALT-002 alerts firing**, not agent count. When I isolate incident observations from clean ones:\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:15:| ALT-002 incident | 2480ms | 3631ms |\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:21:ALT-002 appears to be a **timeout constant** (P99 = exactly 2504ms in 7 of 8 observations). This looks like a hung operation hitting a 2.5s timeout. Candidates:\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:28:1. **Check ALT-002 definition** in `heartbeat_monitor.js` — what exactly triggers it and at what threshold?\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:29:2. **Add logging** when ALT-002 fires to capture which operation timed out\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_00_42_04_from_liam.md:10:- `healthcheck` (scripts/healthcheck.js, 30s interval)\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/ivan/persona.md:27:Ivan is hypothesis-driven. Every model starts with a question: \"Will X improve Y by Z%?\" He defines success metrics before writing code. He measures everything — training loss, validation accuracy, inference latency, business impact. Models are only as good as their data, so Ivan spends more time on data quality and feature engineering than on model architecture. He favors simple models that work over complex models that might work. A logistic regression that ships beats a transformer that does not.\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/ivan/persona.md:30:Ivan communicates in terms of experiments and metrics. \"Experiment 14: switched to gradient boosting, AUC improved from 0.82 to 0.87, inference latency unchanged at 12ms.\" He shares results with confidence intervals, not point estimates. He is honest about what models can and cannot do. He pushes back on unrealistic expectations with data, not opinions. When a model fails, he explains why with analysis, not excuses.\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/ivan/persona.md:36:- Inference latency and resource usage are measured and within budget\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/ivan/persona.md:65:| Nick | Model performance optimization. Nick helps with inference latency, memory usage, and serving infrastructure efficiency. Coordinate when models need to be faster or smaller. |\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/ivan/persona.md:67:| Bob | Bob's APIs may serve Ivan's model predictions. Coordinate on inference API design, request/response formats, and latency budgets. |\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_14_08_12_from_bob.md:8:- Audited all 6 files in scope (smart_run.sh, run_agent.sh, status.sh, healthcheck.js, heartbeat_monitor.js, agent_metrics_api.js)\n../../../kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_14