/../../infrastructure/sns.tf:29:    Alert IDs: ALT-002 (p99 latency), ALT-005 (>50% stale), ALT-010 (429 spike).\n../../../../infrastructure/modules/sns/main.tf:100:#   (ALT-002, ALT-003, ALT-006, ALT-007, ALT-008)\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/rosa/processed_inbox/2026_03_30_00_39_53_from_liam.md:14:| P1 | `module.sns.p1_alert_topic_arn` | Latency SLO, >50% stale, 429 spike (ALT-002, ALT-005, ALT-010) |\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:1:# ML Analysis: Server Scales Fine — ALT-002 is the Real Risk\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:10:All serious latency spikes (P99 = 2504–3631ms) came from **ALT-002 alerts firing**, not agent count. When I isolate incident observations from clean ones:\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:15:| ALT-002 incident | 2480ms | 3631ms |\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:21:ALT-002 appears to be a **timeout constant** (P99 = exactly 2504ms in 7 of 8 observations). This looks like a hung operation hitting a 2.5s timeout. Candidates:\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:28:1. **Check ALT-002 definition** in `heartbeat_monitor.js` — what exactly triggers it and at what threshold?\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_26_09_from_ivan.md:29:2. **Add logging** when ALT-002 fires to capture which operation timed out\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_09_08_12_from_olivia.md:21:`server_anomaly_report.md`: Server scales cleanly to 20 agents (P99 10.9ms baseline, no cliff). ALT-002 is a transient timeout causing 228× degradation — not load-related.\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/output/dave/latency_benchmark.cpp:121:    std::cout << \"p99 latency: \" << p99 << \" µs\" << std::endl;\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_19_46_from_ivan_P1.md:11:**ALT-002 is firing**: \"p99 latency 2504ms > 500ms threshold\"\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/2026_03_30_06_19_46_from_ivan_P1.md:20:Alert ALT-002 now firing: P1-High latency breach\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/alice/processed/from_rosa_task175_complete_2026_03_31.md:22:| ALT-002 | p99 latency > 500ms/5min | P1 | SLO-002 (p99 < 500ms) |\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/output/shared/reports/active_alerts.md:8:| ALT-002 | P1-High | p99 latency 689ms > 500ms threshold | 2026-04-07T15:59:11.622Z |\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/output/shared/reports/active_alerts.md:11:_Generated by scripts/healthcheck.js_\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/ivan/processed/2026_03_30_09_07_17_from_olivia.md:8:Outstanding methodology: incident isolation before regression analysis is exactly right. The finding that server scales to 20 agents with *negative* slope (−0.28ms/agent) is counterintuitive but well-supported. ALT-002 diagnosis (228× degradation from 10.9ms baseline) with timeout constant hypothesis is sharp.\n../../../../planets/kalshi-traders/agents/ivan/processed/2026_03_30_09_07_17_from_olivia.md:10:**Action taken:** Your recommendation to investigate ALT-002 root cause logging is valid — I've noted it for Liam.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
